# ShellCheck config for the night-shift engine.
# Target shell is bash (macOS bash 3.2+ locally, bash on Linux CI). Only these
# three codes are disabled repo-wide — each is a categorical false positive in
# this codebase (80+ sites combined). Every other check stays ON so the CI gate
# still catches real bugs; localized intentional cases use inline pragmas.

# jq filter strings are single-quoted on purpose: `$x` inside them is a jq
# variable bound by --arg / --argjson, NOT a shell variable. Expansion is
# intentionally avoided, so SC2016 ("expressions don't expand in single quotes")
# is always wrong here.
disable=SC2016

# NOTE: SC2318 (single-line `local a=$1 b=$a`) is NOT disabled here — it is a
# real bug in production code, so the gate keeps it ON. Its only occurrences are
# in scripts/test/fixtures.sh (which works by dynamic scoping); the suppression
# is scoped to that file's own header directive, not repo-wide.

# The atomic-write idiom `jq ... >"$tmp" && mv "$tmp" "$dst" || die` is used
# throughout: the `||` branch firing on EITHER a failed write or a failed move is
# the intended fail-closed behavior, not the if/else mix-up SC2015 warns about.
disable=SC2015
